    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a pot with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> butter </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once melted, add 2 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span><strong> flour </strong>with the <strong>remaining chopped thyme</strong> and cook for 30 secs until a paste forms</p><p>Add the <strong>stock </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook for 6-8 min or until thickened – this is your<strong> gravy</strong></p><p>Once thickened, remove the gravy from the heat and set aside</p>",
